{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Formative feedback, a pedagogical approach that facilitates the bridging of gaps in understanding and fosters metacognitive processes in students, has a rich historical context and theoretical framework (Butler & Winne, 1995; Hattie & Timperley, 2007; Narciss, 2008; Wisniewski et al., 2020).",
    "Designed to stimulate cognitive processes and deepen understanding, formative feedback and various learning scaffolds enhance selfregulated learning (SRL) (Hattie & Timperley, 2007; Wisniewski et al., 2020), a subject of intensive study in educational psychology (Ifenthaler, 2012; Lehmann & I. Hähnlein et al., 2014; Zimmerman, 2002).",
    "In light of the efficacy of appropriately structured feedback, digital learning platforms have progressively incorporated automated feedback systems to simulate the formative feedback inherent in traditional pedagogical contexts (Deeva et al., 2021; Steinert et al., 2024a).",
    "In the contemporary era, the emergence of LLMs, distinguished by their superior linguistic performance, offers a promising trajectory for the development of intelligent tutoring systems.",
    "These advanced systems, transcending the capabilities of conventional automated feedback mechanisms, have the potential to stimulate SRL through the strategic implementation of formative feedback."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Formative feedback, a pedagogical approach that facilitates the bridging of gaps in understanding and fosters metacognitive processes in students, has a rich historical context and theoretical framework (Butler & Winne, 1995; Hattie & Timperley, 2007; Narciss, 2008; Wisniewski et al., 2020).",
    "Designed to stimulate cognitive processes and deepen understanding, formative feedback and various learning scaffolds enhance selfregulated learning (SRL) (Hattie & Timperley, 2007; Wisniewski et al., 2020), a subject of intensive study in educational psychology (Ifenthaler, 2012; Lehmann & I. Hähnlein et al., 2014; Zimmerman, 2002).",
    "In light of the efficacy of appropriately structured feedback, digital learning platforms have progressively incorporated automated feedback systems to simulate the formative feedback inherent in traditional pedagogical contexts (Deeva et al., 2021; Steinert et al., 2024a)."
